=Description=

"Critical Labour Studies (CLS) is a network of researchers and trade unionists.
 
The Critical Labour Studies symposium aims to bring together researchers and activists to discuss key features of work and employment from a radical and labour-focused perspective.  It attempts to provide links between the activities of trade unionists, activists, universities, and researchers, allowing a broad and critical debate to emerge."
(http://criticallabourstudies.org.uk/site/)


